{
  "stem": "15962.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And just like a mother tries to protect her own child [BACKROUND NOISE] before giving shelter to a foreigner, these groups acted similarly and in a way helped orphans, if I can call myself that, or those unprotected children, to sort of form almost a gang that if somebody could steal half a loaf of bread or a slice of bread or a pair of gloves, they would bring it to the group.",
      "word_count": 73
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this way, there was also a feeling that you were part of something.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think the loneliness and uniqueness of the situation is much more scary than if you know that somebody else is with you.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's like if suddenly the electricity is turned off, you always look on the street.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And if I see that whole street is dark, I feel much better than if it's just my house.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were now back in Mauthausen, on a-- a wet, slippery slope in tents.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One day, we were suddenly ordered to keep moving, down the hill, to a opening in the [BACKROUND NOISE] [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] barbed wire fence and counted in batches of, say, 100 and guards assigned to us.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were marched out of Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "By this time, our guards were mostly older men that were just recruited, for lack of able-bodied soldiers that were all at the front or in other jobs.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were sent on a march, not knowing where we are going.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We went again through the town.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "By that time, the town looked a little grimmer and less prosperous and was full of military and other vehicles.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Streets were clogged with refugees.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And these proud Austrians no longer looked quite so proud as they did on our trip a few months earlier.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
